      • connect

        public boolean connect()
        connect and open a websocket connection with the millicast platform. returning true does not mean you are connected. You must set valid credentials before using this method.
        Returns:
        false if an error occured, true otherwise. You are connected when the Listener's method on_connected is called.

      • connect

        public abstract boolean connect​(Client.JsonData data)
        Connect to millicast with data return by the director api (websocket url and JWT) Useful if you call the director api yourself (without using the sdk) or use another service
        Parameters:
        data - The Json Data
        Returns:
        true if success false otherwise

      • getStats

        public void getStats​(int timems)
        Enable the collection of stats over a specific time interval. The stats are collected once the client is either publishing or subscribed.
        Parameters:
        timems - The time in ms. If it is 0, the collection will stop
